<%# A removable applied-filter chip, shared by the events filter and the rule
    form so the two read identically. Carries its own hidden field (param =
    s[]/q[]/l[]/d[]) so it submits with the surrounding form; the leading icon is
    derived from that param. The whole chip is the remove control — a <button>
    that dispatches to the tag-picker controller, which strips the chip (and, on
    the events filter, re-submits); the × is a decorative affordance. A type=hidden
    input is non-interactive, so it nests in the button and still submits.

    Locals: param, value, and an optional label (date chips show a localized
    label while submitting the raw range value). The tag-picker controller builds
    the same markup client-side for picks made without a round-trip.

    input: false renders a display-only chip with no hidden field — used for the
    rule form's window tag, where the <select> already carries d[]. remove_action
    overrides the × handler for that case (clear the select rather than drop a
    chip). %>
<button type="button" class="tag active" data-tag-chip
        aria-label="<%= value %>"
        data-action="<%= local_assigns.fetch(:remove_action, 'tag-picker#remove') %>">
  <% if local_assigns.fetch(:input, true) %><%= hidden_field_tag param, value, id: nil %><% end %>
  <span class="<%= filter_chip_icon(param, value) %>" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span><%= local_assigns.fetch(:label, value) %></span>
  <span class="tag__remove ph ph-x" aria-hidden="true"></span>
</button>
